# Part 2: The Critical Bug We Will Fix

## The Problem

The crawler will find 0 links from [https://codetrainafrica.com/](https://codetrainafrica.com/) despite the HTML containing navigation links. After debugging, we will discover:

**Root Cause:** The crawler will remove `<nav>` HTML elements to clean up text content, but ALL the internal navigation links will be inside those `<nav>` elements.

```python
# BROKEN CODE - removed nav before extracting links
for script in soup(["script", "style", "nav", "footer"]):
    script.decompose()  # This removed the links!

# Then tried to find links
links = soup.find_all("a", href=True)  # Found 0 links
```

**The Fix:** Extract links FIRST, then clean up text.

```python
# FIXED CODE - extract links before removing nav
# Step 1: Extract links
for link in soup.find_all("a", href=True):
    # ... process links ...

# Step 2: NOW remove script/style for text cleaning
for script in soup(["script", "style"]):
    script.decompose()
```

## Impact

- Before fix: Will crawl 1 page, will find 0 links, will give generic responses
- After fix: Will crawl multiple pages, will discover projects/blog/resume, will give specific answers

