# Part 6: Access URLs and Testing

## Running the Complete System

### Terminal 1: Start CodeTrain API
```bash
cd your-project-directory/codetrain-chatbot
source venv/bin/activate
./venv/bin/python server.py
# Runs on http://localhost:8000
```

### Terminal 2: Start Web Server
```bash
cd your-project-directory
python3 -m http.server 9000
# Serves on http://localhost:9000
```

### Terminal 3: Test API
```bash
# Health check
curl http://localhost:8000/api/test

# Ask a question
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/chat \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"question": "What projects has CodeTrain Africa worked on?"}'
```

## Access Points

1. **Website:** http://localhost:9000/cursor-course-welcome.html
2. **Standalone Chat:** http://localhost:8000 (serves static/index.html)
3. **API Docs:** http://localhost:8000/api/test

# Part 7: Key Lessons Learned

## Technical Lessons

1. **Order matters in web scraping** - Extract data before modifying HTML structure
2. **CORS is tricky** - Opening files directly (`file://`) blocks localhost API calls
3. **Always use a web server** - Even for "simple" HTML files
4. **Clear Python cache** - `__pycache__` files hide code changes
5. **Test incrementally** - Debug crawler separately from full system

## Architecture Lessons

1. **Start simple** - Static chatbot proved the concept before adding complexity
2. **Agent pattern is powerful** - Letting AI decide what to explore beats hardcoded logic
3. **Cost vs. quality tradeoff** - LLM calls are expensive but provide better answers
4. **Caching is essential** - Would save 80-90% of API costs in production
5. **Vector search > keyword search** - Semantic understanding beats exact matching

## Prompting Lessons

1. **Be specific** - "Make it look awesome" worked because context was clear
2. **Iterate** - Will start with OpenCode, will switch to CodeTrain Africa, will evolve to CodeTrain
3. **Show examples** - Referencing CodeTrain repo provided clear direction
  4. **Debug together** - Walking through the crawler bug in real-time will fix it faster

# Part 8: Production Deployment Guide

## The Architecture Problem

Your chatbot has two parts that need hosting:

```
┌─────────────────┐         ┌─────────────────┐
│   FRONTEND      │         │    BACKEND      │
│   (HTML/JS)     │  ────>  │  (Python API)   │
│   Port 9000     │  HTTP   │   Port 8000     │
└─────────────────┘         └─────────────────┘
```

**Current setup (localhost):**

- Frontend: `http://localhost:9000/cursor-course-welcome.html`
- Backend: `http://localhost:8000/api/chat`

**Production needs:**

- Frontend: `https://yourclient.com`
- Backend: `https://api.yourclient.com` or `https://yourclient.com/api`

## Hosting Options Overview

| Option | Cost | Difficulty | Best For |
|--------|------|------------|----------|
| **Vercel + Railway** | $5-20/mo | Easy | Small sites, quick deploy |
| **Render (all-in-one)** | Free-$25/mo | Easy | Budget projects |
| **DigitalOcean VPS** | $4-24/mo | Medium | Full control |
| **AWS/AWS Lambda** | $5-50/mo | Hard | Enterprise scale |
| **Railway + Netlify** | $5-15/mo | Easy | Modern stack |

## Option A: Render (Recommended - Easiest)

Render can host both frontend and backend in one place.

### Prepare File Structure
```
chatbot-deploy/
├── backend/
│   ├── server.py
│   ├── jobs.py
│   ├── hustle.py
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   ├── .env (with API key)
│   └── utils/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── web_crawler.py
│       └── call_llm.py
├── frontend/
│   ├── index.html (rename cursor-course-welcome.html)
│   └── static/
│       ├── index.html
│       └── chatbot.js
└── render.yaml
```

### Create render.yaml
```yaml
services:
  # Backend API
  - type: web
    name: sisengai-chatbot-api
    env: python
    buildCommand: pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
    startCommand: cd backend && uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT
    envVars:
      - key: OPENROUTER_API_KEY
        sync: false  # Set manually in dashboard
      - key: OPENROUTER_MODEL
        value: anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet
    plan: starter  # $7/month

  # Frontend Static Site
  - type: web
    name: sisengai-chatbot-frontend
    env: static
    buildCommand: echo "No build needed"
    staticPublishPath: frontend
    routes:
      - type: rewrite
        source: /api/*
        destination: http://sisengai-chatbot-api.onrender.com/api/*
```

### Update Frontend API URL
```javascript
// In frontend/index.html, change:
this.API_URL = 'http://localhost:8000/api';

// To:
this.API_URL = window.location.hostname === 'localhost' 
    ? 'http://localhost:8000/api' 
    : '/api';  // Same domain, will proxy to backend
```

### Deploy Steps
```bash
# 1. Push to GitHub
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOURUSERNAME/sisengai-chatbot.git
git push -u origin main

# 2. Go to render.com
# Click "New" → "Blueprint"
# Connect your GitHub repo
# Add your OPENROUTER_API_KEY in dashboard
# Deploy!
```

### Cost

- **Free tier:** 750 hours/month (testing)
- **Starter plan:** $7/month for backend, free for frontend
- **Total:** $7/month for production

## Option B: Railway (Backend) + Vercel (Frontend)

Separate hosting for more flexibility.

### Deploy Backend to Railway
```bash
# Install Railway CLI
npm install -g @railway/cli

# Login and create project
railway login
cd codetrain-chatbot
railway init

# Add environment variables
railway variables set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-key
railway variables set OPENROUTER_MODEL=anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet

# Deploy
railway up

# Get your URL
railway domain
# Returns: https://your-app.up.railway.app
```

### Deploy Frontend to Vercel
```bash
# Install Vercel CLI
npm install -g vercel

# Deploy
cd ..
vercel

# Get URL: https://sisengai-chatbot.vercel.app
```

### Cost

- **Railway:** $5/month (200GB bandwidth)
- **Vercel:** Free (Hobby plan) or $20/month (Pro)
- **Total:** $5-25/month

## Option C: DigitalOcean VPS (Full Control)

### Create Droplet
```bash
# Go to digitalocean.com
# Create Droplet: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
# Size: $4/month (Basic)
# Add SSH key
```

### Setup Server
```bash
# SSH into server
ssh root@your-droplet-ip

# Update system
apt update && apt upgrade -y

# Install dependencies
apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv nginx -y

# Create app directory
mkdir -p /var/www/chatbot
cd /var/www/chatbot

# Upload code
scp -r codetrain-chatbot/* root@your-droplet-ip:/var/www/chatbot/

# Setup virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Create .env file
nano .env
# Add your API key
```

### Create Systemd Service
```bash
nano /etc/systemd/system/chatbot.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=CodeTrain Africa Chatbot API
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/var/www/chatbot
Environment="PATH=/var/www/chatbot/venv/bin"
ExecStart=/var/www/chatbot/venv/bin/uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

```bash
systemctl daemon-reload
systemctl start chatbot
systemctl enable chatbot
```

### Configure Nginx
```bash
nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/chatbot
```

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name yourdomain.com www.yourdomain.com;

    # Frontend
    location / {
        root /var/www/chatbot/frontend;
        index index.html;
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }

    # Backend API
    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}
```

```bash
ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/chatbot /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
nginx -t
systemctl restart nginx
```

### Add SSL (Free)
```bash
apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y
certbot --nginx -d yourdomain.com -d www.yourdomain.com
```

### Cost
- **Droplet:** $4-24/month
- **Domain:** $10-15/year
- **SSL:** Free (Let's Encrypt)
- **Total:** $4-24/month

## Option D: AWS Lambda (Serverless)

### Install Serverless Framework
```bash
npm install -g serverless
```

### Create serverless.yml
```yaml
service: sisengai-chatbot

provider:
  name: aws
  runtime: python3.11
  stage: prod
  region: us-east-1
  environment:
    OPENROUTER_API_KEY: ${env:OPENROUTER_API_KEY}

functions:
  chat:
    handler: handler.chat
    events:
      - http:
          path: api/chat
          method: post
          cors: true
    timeout: 30
    memorySize: 512
```

### Deploy
```bash
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-key
serverless deploy
```

### Cost
- **Lambda:** ~$0.20 per 1M requests
- **API Gateway:** $3.50 per 1M requests
- **First year:** Likely free (free tier)
- **Typical:** $1-10/month for moderate traffic

