## CORS Configuration

For client websites, update `server.py`:
```python
from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware

app.add_middleware(
    CORSMiddleware,
    allow_origins=[
        "https://clientwebsite.com",
        "https://www.clientwebsite.com"
    ],
    allow_credentials=True,
    allow_methods=["*"],
    allow_headers=["*"],
)
```

## Docker Deployment (Universal)

### Dockerfile
```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

COPY . .

EXPOSE 8000
CMD ["uvicorn", "server:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
```

### docker-compose.yml
```yaml
version: '3.8'

services:
  backend:
    build: ./codetrain-chatbot
    ports:
      - "8000:8000"
    environment:
      - OPENROUTER_API_KEY=${OPENROUTER_API_KEY}
    restart: always

  frontend:
    image: nginx:alpine
    ports:
      - "80:80"
    volumes:
      - ./cursor-course-welcome.html:/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html:ro
    depends_on:
      - backend
```

### Deploy
```bash
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-key
docker-compose up -d
```

## Deployment Checklist

### Before Deploying
- [ ] Test locally on different ports
- [ ] Update API URLs for production
- [ ] Add CORS allowed origins
- [ ] Set environment variables securely
- [ ] Add error logging (Sentry, LogDNA)
- [ ] Set up monitoring (Uptime Robot)

### Security Checklist
- [ ] Never commit .env files
- [ ] Use HTTPS (SSL certificates)
- [ ] Rate limit API endpoints
- [ ] Validate user inputs
- [ ] Set up CORS properly

